comment: The complex numbers form a set. This axiom is redundant in the presence of the other axioms (see ~ cnexALT ), but the proof requires the axiom of replacement, while the derivation from the construction here does not. Thus, we can avoid ~ ax-rep in later theorems by invoking the axiom ~ ax-cnex instead of ~ cnexALT . Use ~ cnex instead. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 17-Nov-2014.) (New usage is discouraged.)
